    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>The Nottingham Congregational Church was formed in Cleveland, Ohio, in 1908. The Euclid
        Congregational Church was formed in Euclid, Ohio, in 1915. In 1952, the church constructed a
        new building. In 1960, the Euclid Congregational Church and the Nottingham Congregational
        Church merged to form the Hope Congregational Church in Euclid, Ohio. In 1990, the Hope
        Congregational Church merged into the Faith United Church of Christ in Richmond Heights,
        Ohio. Faith United Church of Christ and the Lyndhurst Community Presbyterian Church merged
        in 2020 to form the Lyndhurst Community of Faith Church.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>This collection contains records related to the Nottingham Congregational Church, the
        Euclid Congregational Church, and the Hope Congregational Church which was formed from the
        merging of the two previous churches. The collection includes a record book from the
        Nottingham Congregational Church, as well as two folders of loose materials removed from
        that record book, a scrapbook for the Euclid Congregational Church, a letter describing the
        decision to merge, and a membership directory.</p>
    </scopecontent>
